Spring Test — Basic to Advanced

What is Spring Test?

Spring Test is the official testing framework support module for the Spring ecosystem
It bridges JUnit / TestNG with the Spring ApplicationContext, dependency injection, and web layer
Spring Boot extends it further with @SpringBootTest, auto-configuration, test slices, and embedded servers
Goal is to test your Spring code as close to production behaviour as possible without deploying anywhere

Testing Pyramid — Where Each Test Lives:

                          ┌─────────┐
                          │   E2E   │  ← few, slow, full system
                          │  Tests  │    (Selenium, Postman)
                         /└─────────┘\
                        /             \
                       /  Integration  \
                      /     Tests       \  ← @SpringBootTest
                     /  @WebMvcTest      \   @DataJpaTest
                    /   @DataJpaTest      \
                   /─────────────────────  \
                  /                         \
                 /       Unit Tests          \  ← @ExtendWith(Mockito)
                /   (Mockito, plain JUnit)    \   pure Java, no context
               └─────────────────────────────--┘

  Unit Tests        → fast, isolated, no Spring context, mock everything
  Integration Tests → Spring context loads, real beans, real DB (H2/TC)
  E2E Tests         → full app running, external systems, browser/HTTP

