Context Caching — How Spring Reuses Contexts
  Spring caches the ApplicationContext between tests
  Same context config = same cached context = FAST

  CONTEXT IS REUSED when:
  ─────────────────────────
  Same @SpringBootTest config
  Same @ActiveProfiles
  Same @TestPropertySource values
  No @MockBean differences
  → Test suite runs much faster (context loads once)

  CONTEXT IS RECREATED when:
  ────────────────────────────
  Different @SpringBootTest(classes=...)
  Different @ActiveProfiles("x") vs @ActiveProfiles("y")
  Different set of @MockBean
  @DirtiesContext used explicitly

  @DirtiesContext
  ─────────────────
  Forces context to be destroyed and recreated after test
  Use ONLY when your test mutates global Spring state
  Very expensive — avoid unless absolutely necessary

  @DirtiesContext(classMode = AFTER_CLASS)   // after all tests in class
  @DirtiesContext(methodMode = AFTER_METHOD) // after each test method

